%T A395125 3176239151670,105332578143513,3534263264246328,119752347674346144,
%U A395125 4091389904212398816,140782658274333029520,4874271390275739192576,169675592305103963489274,5934763165170610698505308
%N A395125 Expansion of 2F1(1/3, 1/3; 1; 27*x/(1-4*x)^3)^2.
%C A395125 Integer sequence arising from the symmetric square of a Gauss hypergeometric function composed with a degree-3 Belyi map phi(x) = 27*x/(1-4*x)^3. Not an Apery-like sequence: no order-2 polynomial recurrence was found with degree <= 12.
%C A395125 It seems that a(n) is odd for n in A145849 +- 1 (checked up to 200) and a multiple of 3 for all n > 0. - _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 13 2026
%H A395125 Alex Shvets, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19387246">Integer sequences from Sym^2(2F1) Belyi pullback scan</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%F A395125 a(n) = [x^n] 2F1(1/3, 1/3; 1; 27*x/(1-4*x)^3)^2.
%e A395125 2F1(1/3, 1/3; 1; 27*x/(1-4*x)^3)^2 = 1 + 6*x + 153*x^2 + 3912*x^3 + ...
%t A395125 CoefficientList[Series[Hypergeometric2F1[1/3, 1/3, 1, 27*x/(1-4*x)^3]^2, {x, 0, 17}], x]
%o A395125 (PARI) Vec(hypergeom([1/3,1/3],1,27*x/(1-4*x)^3)^2) \\ _M. F. Hasler_, Apr 13 2026
%Y A395125 Cf. A145849, A393810, A394679, A394680.
%K A395125 nonn,new
%O A395125 0,2
